---
// coming-soon — variant 13: "Manifesto → Monolith" (the 3 + 4 MERGE, 2026-07-08).
//
// Owner directive: "4 opens → into 3". One continuous composition in two zones:
//   ZONE 1 — the Ticker Manifesto (CsV4): kinetic positioning lines cycle with
//            masked per-line reveals + stanza cadence; a live countdown rides the
//            top-right corner.
//   ZONE 2 — the Monolith Tease (CsV3): a small brass-edged prism turns slowly on
//            a dark stage, "The new site lands 24.07." headline + a plain-spoken
//            top-tier-London-studio positioning, the open-for-business mailto as
//            the closing move (round-3 copy: impactful, friendly, no decode-metaphors).
//
// THE SEAM (one page, not two stacked): the manifesto's LAST stanza gestures
// downward ("The first cut is / turning into view. / Come and see.") and hands
// off into the descent; the prism is a DISCOVERED object — it rises + resolves as
// zone 2 enters (view-timeline reveal), so you arrive to find it, never delivered
// to a finished slide. ONE STAGE LIGHT (round-2 polish): a single soft radial
// (.csm-light) straddles the zone boundary — centred ON the seam, its upper half
// washing the manifesto's foot, its lower half lighting the monolith's stage —
// replacing round 1's two clashing per-zone gradients. On fine pointers the light
// drifts subtly toward the cursor (lerped, §7 Pointer Field restraint), and
// clicking the hello@ mailto makes it swell/brighten for a beat — a small
// "we're open" reinforcement. RM/touch keep the static composed light.
//   (round 4: the light box no longer clips — it spans the whole composition and
//   the radial fades to nothing at both true page ends, so there is no hard cut
//   at top or bottom; the grain plane is radially masked so its box edges never
//   read as a line. round 5: ALL of the light's overflow is caught by .csm's
//   overflow:clip — both axes — because the unclipped transformed box was adding
//   dead scroll below zone 2 on desktop, wrecking the settled bottom.)
//
// SCROLL DRIVES THE STORY IN ZONE 2 (round-2 polish): the whole monolith zone is
// choreographed on a named view-timeline (--csmz2, scrubbed by scroll, pure CSS —
// no JS, portable): the prism's orbit wrapper turns ~150° as you traverse into the
// zone (composing with — never fighting — the 26s idle turn nested inside it), the
// floor line draws in, and the content arrives as MASKED, STAGGERED lifts (each
// line rises out of a clip mask in sequence — wordmark → eyebrow → title → lede →
// datum → contact → CTA), all tied to progress, none on-load. The auto-descent
// therefore doubles as the entrance choreography: the 2.2s carry scrubs the whole
// arrival. Where animation-timeline is unsupported (round 4: some mobile engines,
// notably Safari), a JS rAF scrub reads the monolith's rect on passive scroll and
// drives the SAME choreography (identical scroll-driven orbit on every browser) —
// feature-detected, CSS path stays where supported; round 5 smooths that path
// through a lerped one-pole follower (~150ms) so coarse touch-scroll events read
// butter-fluid, with the 26s idle turn composing inside the scrubbed orbit just
// like desktop. HARD GUARANTEE (round 5): every scrubbed reveal completes at or
// safely before maximum scroll on every viewport (all ranges end ≤42%; the seam
// runway is MOBILE-ONLY; nothing may extend scroll past the monolith's end).
// The "Come and see" cue is gently sticky (round 5): it follows the reader a
// short way toward zone 2 inside a bounded track, releasing at the monolith's
// top edge — always before the prism — then fades as zone 2 takes the screen.
// Under RM everything is simply visible, static (cue static in place).
//
// BRANDING (round-2 polish): no chrome in zone 1 (the manifesto speaks alone); the
// CANONICAL BlazingOwl wordmark (the nav logo geometry, inlined per the surface's
// portability convention — own gradient id, no shared deps) leads zone 2's
// entrance cascade.
//
// TWO PATHS DOWN (both graceful):
//   (a) AUTO — when the manifesto completes its first full pass while the reader is
//       idle, a slow, unhurried programmatic descent (~2.2s easeOut) carries you to
//       the monolith. It is NEVER a scroll-jack mid-reading: it only fires after the
//       last stanza has been read, only from the top, and it YIELDS instantly to any
//       genuine scroll intent (wheel / touch / key / pointer) — the user always wins.
//   (b) MANUAL — you can simply scroll down into the monolith at any moment.
//
// ONE CLOCK, NO DUPLICATES: the live T-minus lives ONLY in the top-right corner
// (zone-1 register). The instant you enter the monolith zone that corner clock
// hides, and zone 2 carries its own "24.07" date register instead — never two
// clocks on screen. (Progress/zone/descent state are exposed as data-csm-* attrs
// for headless verification; they are inert design metadata otherwise.)
//
// SELF-CONTAINED / PORTABLE (the surface convention — the winner ports to a fresh
// standalone repo). The port must carry: Bricolage + Manrope + Geist Mono fonts;
// the Molten Brass tokens (--color-* + rgb triplets, --font-*, --text-*, --ease-*,
// --radius-surface). The CSS-3D prism carries over verbatim from CsV3's
// zero-dependency choice (no WebGL, no runtime deps) so it survives the move
// untouched. No email endpoint (the contact affordance is a mailto).
//
// FLOORS: RM-safe (prefers-reduced-motion → no cycling, no prism turn, NO
// auto-descent; the page is a STATIC COMPOSED PAGE with BOTH zones visible, the
// first stanza revealed, the prism parked three-quarter-on). No-JS-safe (both zones
// are static DOM stacked in flow and reachable by scroll; the first stanza shows;
// the corner clock degrades to the printed launch date). Mobile-first at 390px.
//
// ── STANDALONE PORT (blazingowl.co.uk holding page, 2026-07-09) ──────────────
// Verbatim CsV13 body/style/script, wrapped in a full public document. The four
// variable fonts + the Molten Brass token subset (src/styles/global.css) are the
// only carried deps. Differences from the lab copy: this is the REAL public page
// — indexed (no noindex), full <title>/description/OG, lang en-GB.

// Self-hosted variable fonts (registers the "* Variable" @font-face families the
// --font-* tokens point at; SAME SET as the main repo's Base.astro — Manrope
// (body) + Bricolage (display) + Geist Mono (annotation). Inter was NOT part of
// the main site and was dropped here on 2026-07-09: the port had silently
// switched --font-body to Inter, so the lede/contact/CTA rendered in a different
// (softer-looking) typeface than the homepage. Body text is Manrope, matching
// the main site + the source lab CsV13.
import '@fontsource-variable/manrope'
import '@fontsource-variable/bricolage-grotesque'
import '@fontsource-variable/geist-mono'
import '../styles/global.css'

const title = 'BlazingOwl — London digital design studio'
const description =
	"We're a top-tier London digital design studio — remaking our site to showcase our work and recent projects."
const canonical = 'https://blazingowl.co.uk/'
const ogImage = 'https://blazingowl.co.uk/og-image.jpg'

const statements = [
	['A London studio', 'for brands that', 'refuse the generic.'],
	['Small enough to care,', 'sharp enough', 'to make it count.'],
	['Design that earns awe —', 'then proves it', 'in the numbers.'],
	['The studio is open —', 'the new site', 'is nearly here.'],
]
const target = '2026-07-24T17:00:00+01:00'
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en-GB">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta
			name="viewport"
			content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=5"
		/>
		<title>{title}</title>
		<meta name="description" content={description} />
		<link rel="canonical" href={canonical} />
		<meta name="theme-color" content="#0A0A0A" />
		<meta name="msapplication-TileColor" content="#0A0A0A" />
		<meta
			name="robots"
			content="index, follow, max-image-preview:large, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1"
		/>

		<!-- Icons -->
		<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon-96x96.png" sizes="96x96" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
		<link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest" />

		<!-- Open Graph -->
		<meta property="og:type" content="website" />
		<meta property="og:url" content={canonical} />
		<meta property="og:title" content={title} />
		<meta property="og:description" content={description} />
		<meta property="og:image" content={ogImage} />
		<meta property="og:image:width" content="1200" />
		<meta property="og:image:height" content="630" />
		<meta property="og:site_name" content="BlazingOwl" />
		<meta property="og:locale" content="en_GB" />

		<!-- Twitter -->
		<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
		<meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
		<meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
		<meta name="twitter:image" content={ogImage} />
		<meta name="twitter:creator" content="@blazingowl" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<div
	class="cs csm"
	data-cs-page
	data-csm
	data-csm-zone="1"
	data-csm-descent="idle"
	data-csm-progress="0"
	data-csm-cycle="0"
	aria-label="BlazingOwl — launching soon"
>
	{
		/* ---- Fixed page chrome — the corner clock only (owner: zone 1 carries no
		   brand mark; the wordmark belongs to zone 2's entrance). ---------------- */
	}
	{/* The live countdown — the ONLY clock. Zone-1 register; hides in zone 2. */}
	<p class="csm-clock" data-cs-countdown data-cs-target={target}>
		<span class="csm-clock-static">Launching 24.07.2026</span>
		<span class="csm-clock-live" aria-hidden="true">
			Launch <b data-unit="days">14</b>d
			<b data-unit="hours">00</b>h
			<b data-unit="minutes">00</b>m
			<b data-unit="seconds">00</b>s
		</span>
	</p>

	{
		/* ===== ZONE 1 — the Ticker Manifesto (CsV4 language) ==================== */
	}
	<section class="csm-zone csm-manifesto" aria-label="Studio manifesto">
		<div class="csm-stage" data-csm-ticker>
			{
				statements.map((lines, i) => (
					<p
						class:list={['csm-stmt', { 'is-in': i === 0 }]}
						data-stmt={i}
						aria-hidden={i === 0 ? undefined : 'true'}
					>
						{lines.map((line) => (
							<span class="csm-line">
								<span class="csm-line-ink">{line}</span>
							</span>
						))}
					</p>
				))
			}
			{/* Reserve height so cycling never reflows the stage (tallest stanza). */}
			<p class="csm-stmt csm-ghost" aria-hidden="true">
				{
					statements[0].map((line) => (
						<span class="csm-line">
							<span class="csm-line-ink">{line}</span>
						</span>
					))
				}
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	{
		/* THE SEAM RUNWAY + CUE TRACK (round 5). The track's top overlaps up into
		   the manifesto's foot (negative margin), so the "Come and see" cue still
		   sits in the first viewport where it always did; its lower reach is the
		   seam runway — breathing scroll distance before the monolith arrives,
		   MOBILE-ONLY (owner round 5: the desktop runway regressed the settled
		   bottom; desktop net height is exactly zero). Inside it the cue is gently
		   STICKY: it follows the viewer down the page a short way as they scroll
		   toward zone 2, then releases at the track's end — geometrically BEFORE
		   the prism (the track ends at the monolith's top edge, the prism sits
		   below the zone's top padding) — and fades as zone 2 takes over. RM keeps
		   the cue static in place. The auto-descent reads the monolith's live
		   rect, so it simply carries you across whatever span the track adds. */
	}
	<div class="csm-cue-track" aria-hidden="true">
		<div class="csm-cue">
			<span class="csm-cue-line"></span>
			<span class="csm-cue-label">Come and see</span>
			<span class="csm-cue-chev"></span>
		</div>
	</div>

	{/* ===== ZONE 2 — the Monolith Tease (CsV3 language) ===================== */}
	<section class="csm-zone csm-monolith" aria-labelledby="csm-mo-title">
		{/* Marks the seam crossing for the zone flip (top of the monolith). */}
		<span class="csm-seam" aria-hidden="true"></span>

		{
			/* THE ONE STAGE LIGHT — a single radial straddling the seam (its centre
			   sits exactly on the zone boundary): the upper half washes the
			   manifesto's foot, the lower half lights the monolith. Pointer-follow
			   (--lx/--ly, lerped by JS on fine pointers) + the mailto swell live on
			   the core; .csm's overflow:clip keeps it from widening OR lengthening
			   the page (round 5). */
		}
		<div class="csm-light" aria-hidden="true">
			<span class="csm-light-core"></span>
			{
				/* A faint feTurbulence grain (round-3 de-banding): a static, tiled
				   SVG-noise plane in soft-light at ~3% breaks up the concentric
				   bands the radial leaves on similar-intensity dark surfaces. Pure
				   image — zero per-frame cost. */
			}
			<span class="csm-dither"></span>
		</div>

		<div class="csm-stage3d" aria-hidden="true">
			{
				/* The stage line is the prism's OWN ground line (owner round 3): it
				   lives INSIDE the stage3d box so it tracks the prism's base at every
				   viewport, with the flex gap holding a clamped distance to the
				   wordmark below — no more drifting low on mobile / crowding the
				   wordmark on large desktop. */
			}
			<div class="csm-floor" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			{
				/* The orbit wrapper is the SCROLL-driven turn (~150° across the zone's
				   view-timeline); the prism's own 26s idle turn nests inside it, so
				   the two rotations compose instead of fighting. */
			}
			<div class="csm-orbit">
				<div class="csm-prism">
					<span class="csm-face csm-face-front"></span>
					<span class="csm-face csm-face-right"></span>
					<span class="csm-face csm-face-back"></span>
					<span class="csm-face csm-face-left"></span>
					<span class="csm-face csm-cap csm-cap-top"></span>
					<span class="csm-face csm-cap csm-cap-bottom"></span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		{
			/* The content cascade — each .csm-rev is a clip mask whose child lifts
			   in on the zone's scrubbed view-timeline, staggered in document order:
			   wordmark → eyebrow → title → lede → datum → contact → CTA. */
		}
		<div class="csm-inner">
			<div class="csm-rev csm-rev-1">
				<p class="csm-wordmark">
					{
						/* The canonical BlazingOwl wordmark (nav logo geometry), inlined
					    for portability — own gradient id, no shared deps. */
					}
					<svg
						viewBox="0 0 309.99 64.39"
						xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
						role="img"
						aria-label="BlazingOwl"
					>
						<defs>
							<linearGradient id="csm-wm-g" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
								<stop offset="0%" style="stop-color: var(--color-primary-light)"></stop>
								<stop offset="100%" style="stop-color: var(--color-secondary-light)"
								></stop>
							</linearGradient>
