<style>
	.csm {
		position: relative;
		width: 100%;
		background: var(--color-background);
		color: var(--color-foreground);
		isolation: isolate;
		/* Clip BOTH axes (round 5). Horizontal: the oversized / pointer-drifting
		   light core never widens the page. Vertical — THE round-5 desktop-bottom
		   fix: the 260svh light box is transformed (translateY(-50%)) and
		   transformed bounds COUNT toward the page's scrollable overflow, so on
		   desktops (monolith ≈ 100svh < the light's 130svh lower half) it silently
		   added ~30–40svh of DEAD SCROLL below zone 2 — "absolute bottom" pushed
		   the monolith's upper text off-screen with a black void beneath.
		   overflow:clip removes that contribution; the visual cut lands where the
		   radial is ≥77% of its radius (≈0.1% alpha — invisible, pixel-verified).
		   clip (not hidden) creates NO scroll container, so the sticky cue and
		   the fixed clock keep working. */
		overflow: clip;
